    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="1220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">012.3/11–144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé to the Polish Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-01T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 1, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Poles 24. Please deliver the following message for Prime Minister Mikolajczyk
                    from the President: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Personal for Prime Minister Mikolajczyk from the President. Your message
                            of October 26 is receiving my personal consideration. I very much hope
                            that your problems will be composed satisfactorily. I expect to send you
                            another message soon.”<note n="9" xml:id="d1220fn9">In a memorandum of
                                November 9, Acting Secretary of State Stettinius recalled to the
                                President that “the Polish Government is waiting some further word
                                from you.” A short, suggested message was enclosed for the President
                                to approve, but it was not sent. After another reminder on November
                                15 (<hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1334">p.
                                    1334</ref>) the President approved the communication which was
                                sent to Mikolajczyk on November 17 (<ref target="#pg_1334">
                                    <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>
                                </ref>).</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
